{#-
  Califa Cards human-view template (SPEC.md section C).
  Renders a validated card (a JSON-mode dict) into skill-card.md. The frontmatter
  block is the canonical machine payload; the body below it is the rendered human
  view. Wired to Jinja by skillcard/render.py.

  Every frontmatter leaf goes through the `j` filter (json.dumps): JSON is a
  subset of YAML, so the output is valid YAML that round-trips to the exact value
  (null/bool/number/string-with-colons-or-quotes all handled). Optional keys are
  read with .get() so the template never depends on the schema being imported.
-#}
---
name: {{ card.name | j }}
version: {{ card.version | j }}
summary: {{ card.summary | j }}
owner: {{ card.owner | j }}
repo: { tier: {{ card.repo.tier | j }}, url: {{ card.repo.url | j }} }
license: {{ card.license | j }}
{% if card.get('homepage') is not none %}
homepage: {{ card.get('homepage') | j }}
{% endif %}
source_commit: {{ card.source_commit | j }}
content_hash: {{ card.content_hash | j }}
{% if card.get('signature') is not none %}
signature: {{ card.get('signature') | j }}
{% endif %}
description: {{ card.description | j }}
triggers:
  positive:
{% for p in card.triggers.positive %}
    - {{ p | j }}
{% endfor %}
  negative:
{% for n in card.triggers.negative %}
    - { prompt: {{ n.prompt | j }}, use_instead: {{ n.use_instead | j }} }
{% endfor %}
{% if card.get('inputs') is not none %}
inputs: {{ card.get('inputs') | j }}
{% endif %}
output: { type: {{ card.output.type | j }}, format: {{ card.output.format | j }} }
dependencies: {{ card.dependencies | j }}
external_endpoints: {{ card.external_endpoints | j }}
permissions: { network: {{ card.permissions.network | j }}, shell: {{ card.permissions.shell | j }}, file: {{ card.permissions.file | j }}, env: {{ card.permissions.env | j }}, mcp: {{ card.permissions.mcp | j }} }
{% if card.metrics is none %}
metrics: null
{% else %}
metrics:
  trigger_precision: {{ card.metrics.trigger_precision | j }}
  trigger_recall: {{ card.metrics.trigger_recall | j }}
{% if card.metrics.get('near_miss_precision') is not none %}
  near_miss_precision: {{ card.metrics.get('near_miss_precision') | j }}
{% endif %}
  task_completion_rate: {{ card.metrics.task_completion_rate | j }}
{% if card.metrics.get('tool_call_delta') is not none %}
  tool_call_delta: {{ card.metrics.get('tool_call_delta') | j }}
{% endif %}
{% if card.metrics.get('token_efficiency') is not none %}
  token_efficiency: {{ card.metrics.get('token_efficiency') | j }}
{% endif %}
  eval_pass_rate: {{ card.metrics.eval_pass_rate | j }}
  harness: {{ card.metrics.harness | j }}
{% if card.metrics.get('notes') is not none %}
  notes: {{ card.metrics.get('notes') | j }}
{% endif %}
{% endif %}
scan:
  tool: {{ card.scan.tool | j }}
  score: {{ card.scan.score | j }}
  severity: {{ card.scan.severity | j }}
  date: {{ card.scan.date | j }}
  sarif: {{ card.scan.sarif | j }}
{% if card.scan.findings %}
  findings:
{% for f in card.scan.findings %}
    - { rule_id: {{ f.rule_id | j }}, severity: {{ f.severity | j }}, status: {{ f.status | j }}, owasp: {{ f.owasp | j }}, atlas: {{ f.atlas | j }}, note: {{ f.note | j }} }
{% endfor %}
{% else %}
  findings: []
{% endif %}
status: {{ card.status | j }}
card_version: {{ card.card_version | j }}
updated: {{ card.updated | j }}
---

# {{ card.name }} <small>v{{ card.version }}</small>

{{ card.summary }}

**Status:** {{ card.status }} | **License:** {{ card.license }} | **Scan:** {{ card.scan.severity }} ({{ card.scan.score }}/100)

## When to use it

{{ card.description }}

{% if card.metrics is not none %}
## Quality scorecard

| Metric | Value |
| --- | --- |
| Trigger precision | {{ card.metrics.trigger_precision }} |
| Trigger recall | {{ card.metrics.trigger_recall }} |
{% if card.metrics.get('near_miss_precision') is not none %}
| Near-miss precision | {{ card.metrics.get('near_miss_precision') }} |
{% endif %}
| Task completion | {{ card.metrics.task_completion_rate }} |
| Eval pass rate | {{ card.metrics.eval_pass_rate }} |

Harness: `{{ card.metrics.harness }}`
{% if card.metrics.get('notes') is not none %}

> **Caveat.** {{ card.metrics.get('notes') }}
{% endif %}
{% endif %}

## Security

SkillSpector scan `{{ card.scan.tool }}` scored {{ card.scan.score }}/100 ({{ card.scan.severity }} band).

{% if card.scan.findings %}
Findings:

{% for f in card.scan.findings %}
- `{{ f.rule_id }}` ({{ f.severity }}, {{ f.status }}){{ (" — " ~ f.note) if f.note else "" }}
{% endfor %}
{% else %}
No findings.
{% endif %}

The SARIF report lives at `{{ card.scan.sarif }}`.
